{
  "text": "The 3 J H4\u2032H5\u2032 / \u2032\u2032 coupling is very sensitive to the \u03b3 torsion (11, [CITATION_1] . When the \u03b3 torsion is in gauche + conformation, there will be no strong couplings between H4\u2032 and any of the H5's (1.0-2.5 Hz) while both trans and gauche -will result in a strong (\u223c10 Hz) coupling between the H4\u2032 and one of the H5's. No strong 3 J H4\u2032H5\u2032 / \u2032\u2032 could be confirmed for any residue for either ssDNA or ssRNA. It should however be noted that this region is severely crowded, especially for RNA.",
  "citation_candidates": [
